// =============================================================================
// core/proof/mod.vr — Stdlib surface for the verification kernel
// =============================================================================
// Layer: Standard Library / Proof
// =============================================================================
//
// User-facing entry point for compile-time + runtime proof tooling.
// The compiler owns the SMT/kernel pipeline; this module exposes
// ergonomic Verum-level handles so user code can:
//
//   * Reference older snapshot state in postconditions via `old(...)`
//     (`contracts_old.vr` — surface for `verum_types.contracts_old`).
//   * Bundle Necula-style proof certificates with bytecode
//     (`pcc.vr` — Proof-Carrying Code over a content-addressed
//     `Map<GoalHash, ProofCertificate>`).
//   * Reflect a function as an SMT-LIB axiom for use in proof tactics
//     (`reflection.vr` — `reflected_fn` with sort-safety + injection-
//     prevention guards).
//   * Tactic library composition (`tactics/` — combinators, default
//     tactics, custom-tactic registration).
//   * Kernel-bridge primitives that translate between AST proof terms
//     and the internal kernel's term language (`kernel_bridge.vr`).
//
// All modules in this surface are re-export-only at the umbrella
// level: a downstream consumer can pick which sub-surface to import,
// matching the rest of the stdlib's "explicit dependencies, no
// magic prelude" rule.
// =============================================================================

module core.proof;

public module contracts_old;
public module kernel_bridge;
public module pcc;
public module reflection;
public module tactics;
